# changelog

## 2026-05-31

- Implemented Post-MVP 3.2 real ToolRegistry integration with explicit real-tool registry construction, provider settings, normalized tool errors, in-memory TTL caching, DoxAtlas HTTP tool clients, SEC/FRED/BLS/BEA/Fed/Polymarket/Alpha/FMP/Finnhub/Tavily/yfinance tool clients, and agent permission updates while preserving mock-first defaults.
- Added Phase 3.2 real-tool contract tests and marked free-tier smoke tests behind `DOXAGENT_RUN_REAL_API_TESTS=1` so normal test runs remain offline and quota-safe.
- Added real provider environment placeholders plus `yfinance` and `websockets` dependencies for HK-only yfinance snapshots and bounded Finnhub trade-stream capture.
- Split the Phase 3.2 real tool implementation into `tools/factory.py` and per-provider modules under `tools/providers/`, while keeping `tools/real.py` as a compatibility export layer for existing imports.
- Tightened DoxAtlas real tool configuration against `DOXATLAS_TOOL_SCHEMAS.md`, including per-endpoint payload validation, DoxAtlas error-envelope mapping, alias endpoint checks, and read-only default agent authorization for run tools.

## 2026-05-29

- Added `dev_plan/DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md` with a phased development plan based on `dev_plan/PRD.md`, including architecture boundaries, MVP order, core module rollout, stabilization, and final external-agent adapter integration strategy.
- Created `dev_plan/DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md` in the workspace with a detailed phased plan from PRD requirements; noted that external GitHub agent analysis and adapter work must happen only after the core DoxAgent contracts, Blackboard service, workflow, and validation layers are stable.
- Implemented the Phase 0 project baseline: Python 3.11 `uv` configuration, `src/doxagent` package skeleton, baseline tests, local environment template, README setup instructions, Phase 0 boundary document, and mock-first external capability policy.
- Narrowed the Phase 0 Microsoft Agent Framework dependency to `agent-framework-core>=1.6,<2` after the all-in-one `agent-framework` meta package pulled optional Azure integrations that failed dependency resolution and exceeded the minimal-runtime scope.
- Added explicit Ruff exclusions for `.uv-cache`, `.venv`, and external reference sources so workspace-wide linting checks only DoxAgent-owned code and tests.
- Implemented Phase 1 domain contracts with Pydantic models for AgentTask, AgentResult, BlackboardPatch, EvidenceRef, Objection, Delegation, Commit Log entries, Working Memory entries, Belief State snapshots, and the five PRD work document schemas.
- Added Phase 1 stateless promotion-blocking helpers plus contract fixtures and tests covering required fields, JSON round trips, evidence source types, and objection/delegation blocking behavior.
- Added `dev_plan/PHASE1_CONTRACTS.md` and README notes documenting the schema boundary, ID strategy, structured document field strategy, and Phase 1 non-goals.
- Implemented Phase 2 Model Gateway contracts and async client boundary, including standard request/response models, normalized gateway errors, usage and audit summaries, mock client, OpenAI and Anthropic SDK adapters, JSON response normalization, retry/fallback orchestration, and centralized LangSmith provider wrapping.
- Added offline Phase 2 gateway tests with fake provider SDK clients covering mock responses, fallback behavior, non-retryable failures, JSON parsing errors, provider request mapping, and tracing metadata extraction.
- Added `dev_plan/PHASE2_GATEWAY.md` and README notes documenting the Model Gateway boundary, mock-first provider strategy, fallback/error handling, and audit-vs-Commit-Log separation.
- Implemented Phase 3 in-memory Blackboard Service with run initialization, Working Memory writes, Belief State patch submission, permission/evidence/ticker/blocker validation, dot-path patch application, Commit Log creation, and objection/delegation lifecycle helpers.
- Added Phase 3 state transition tests covering Working Memory versus Belief State separation, patch validation failures, Commit Log behavior, unresolved objection blocking, active delegation blocking, and lifecycle unblock/retry behavior.
- Added `dev_plan/PHASE3_BLACKBOARD_SERVICE.md` and README notes documenting the in-memory repository boundary, patch submission rules, dot-path behavior, lifecycle semantics, and Phase 3 non-goals.
- Implemented Phase 4 agent runtime boundaries with default agent definitions, registry lookup, mock runner, and a MAF adapter placeholder that preserves the DoxAgent `AgentTask -> AgentResult` contract.
- Added Phase 4 Context Builder snapshots and mock tool registry contracts, including permission-bounded context summaries, allowed-tool enforcement, and `ToolResult` to `EvidenceRef` conversion.
- Added `dev_plan/PHASE4_AGENT_RUNTIME.md`, README notes, and Phase 4 tests covering registry behavior, runner boundaries, context scoping, tool permissions, evidence conversion, and Blackboard non-mutation.
- Implemented Phase 5 Blackboard initialization workflow MVP with fixed node ordering, in-memory checkpoint/resume, deterministic mock agent outputs, Working Memory writes, Belief State promotion through Blackboard patches, and run summaries.
- Added Phase 5 document dependency checks and blocker handling so unresolved objections or active delegations stop expectation promotion until the Blackboard lifecycle is resolved.
- Added `dev_plan/PHASE5_INITIALIZATION_WORKFLOW.md`, README notes, and Phase 5 tests covering full mock ticker completion, dependency ordering, checkpoint JSON round-trip, blocked resume, and O2 monitoring policy write permissions.
- Implemented Phase 6 mock ticker vertical slice with fixture input data, a `python -m doxagent.examples.phase6_mock_run` entrypoint, and a review-oriented exporter for workflow and Blackboard state.
- Added `examples/phase6_mock_ticker/generated_run.json` showing five document outputs, evidence refs, Working Memory summaries, Commit Log entries, objection/delegation lifecycle summaries, and residual risk notes.
- Added `dev_plan/PHASE6_E2E_SAMPLE.md`, README sample-run instructions, and Phase 6 tests covering module output, review JSON shape, audit visibility, and no broker/trade execution fields.
- Implemented Phase 7 in-memory audit query APIs for Commit Log records, stable field traceability, unresolved objection reports, and blocking delegation reports.
- Added Phase 7 run debug reports and workflow contract failure semantics for failed agent results, missing Blackboard patches, missing evidence, dependency violations, and blocked checkpoint recovery.
- Added `dev_plan/PHASE7_STABILITY_AUDIT_RECOVERY.md`, README notes, and Phase 7 tests covering audit traceability, non-mutating failure behavior, partial retry without duplicate commits, and business-audit versus tracing boundaries.
- Implemented Phase 8's first Vibe-Trading adapters with DoxAgent-owned specs for `macro_rates_fx_desk` and `fundamental_research_team`, deterministic DAG execution, `MacroContextAgentModule`, and `FundamentalBriefAgentModule`.
- Added Phase 8 structured result schemas, AgentResult wrapping, agent-output evidence refs, adapter boundary tests, and documentation for the read-only external reference migration strategy.
- Implemented the Phase 8 financial-services Market Researcher adapter as `IndustryResearchAgentModule`, with a DoxAgent-owned industry research workflow, mock data provider, source refs, confidence, unknowns, and downstream handoff hints.
- Added financial-services industry research schemas, AgentResult wrapping, evidence refs, adapter boundary tests, and documentation for future DoxAtlas/CapIQ/FactSet provider replacement.
- Implemented the Phase 8 native O4 market trace agent with quote, OHLCV, multi-quote provider contracts, deterministic fixture data, Yahoo chart parsing, relative performance, volume analysis, technical signals, valuation context, source refs, and unknown handling.
- Updated the O4 registry output schema to `MarketTraceResult` and added O4 market trace tests plus documentation while keeping Hermes runtime, trading execution, monitoring, and Blackboard writes out of scope.
- Implemented Post-MVP 3.1 persistence foundations with environment-backed storage settings, a Blackboard repository protocol, a transaction-oriented Postgres/Supabase repository, and retained the in-memory repository for local tests.
- Added separate workflow checkpoint repositories for in-memory and Postgres persistence, wired checkpoint history/latest saving into the initialization workflow, and added `resume_latest` support.
- Added the Supabase/Postgres migration for the dedicated `doxagent` schema, split Blackboard business state from workflow checkpoints, and added persistence boundary tests without embedding real Supabase credentials.
- Implemented Post-MVP 3.3 Skill Registry and injection boundaries with versioned skill definitions, default agent skill ids, `AgentTask` skill bundles, MockRunner skill visibility, and Context Builder skill summaries.
- Registered migrated Vibe-Trading, financial-services, and Hermes/O4 skills in the DoxAgent-owned static registry, while keeping external source trees out of runtime.
- Added skill version metadata to Vibe, financial-services, and O4 adapter outputs plus tests and documentation for skill registry, injection, and adapter compatibility.
